# Git & PR Standards

## Never Push a Broken Build

Before pushing or opening a PR, verify locally:

```
lint → typecheck → tests → build
```

All four must pass. Do not skip hooks or CI checks.

## Commit Message Format

Use conventional prefixes with scope:

```
feat(asset): add bulk import endpoint
fix(booking): prevent overlap on concurrent creates
refactor(auth): extract permission policy to domain layer
test(allocation): add department-scoped authorization cases
```

Scopes: `asset`, `booking`, `allocation`, `auth`, `maintenance`, `audit`, or the module name.

## PR Requirements

Every PR must:

- Pass lint, typecheck, tests, and build in CI
- Include tests for new business rules (not just CRUD)
- Keep changes focused — one concern per PR when possible
